Food Products Company Syral Tops U.K. Subsidy List, Defra Says

-- B y   T o n y   C .   D r e i b u s
-- 
2011-08-04T16:59:06Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-04/food-products-company-syral-tops-u-k-subsidy-list-defra-says.html
Syral UK Ltd., a food-products
company, was the largest recipient of U.K. farm-subsidy payments
in 2010, according to the Department for Environment, Food and
Rural Affairs.  Syral received 18.7 million pounds ($30.5 million) in
Common Agricultural Policy payments in 2010, according to the
Defra website. The company, which became Tereos Syral in March,
has a U.K. facility in Selby, North Yorkshire, according to the
companyâ€™s website.  Syral was not immediately available to comment.  Food manufacturer Nestle UK Ltd. received 140,437 pounds in
CAP payments and Czarnikow Group Ltd., a sugar merchant, was
given 337,615 pounds, according to the Defra website. Neither
company was immediately available to comment.  To contact the reporter on this story:
